# lib/generators/correlation_tracker/templates/README
===============================================================================
  CorrelationTracker has been installed!
===============================================================================

  The initializer has been created at:
                                     config/initializers/correlation_tracker.rb

Next steps:

1. Review and customize the configuration
2. Restart your Rails server
3. Correlation IDs will automatically be tracked across:
                                                   - HTTP requests
- Background jobs (ActiveJob, Sidekiq)
- Kafka messages
- Outbound HTTP calls

Usage examples:

        # Get current correlation ID
        CorrelationTracker.current_id

# Manually set correlation context
CorrelationTracker.set(correlation_id: 'custom-id', origin_type: 'cron')

# Execute code with temporary correlation
CorrelationTracker.with_correlation(correlation_id: 'temp-id') do
  # your code here
end

For Faraday HTTP clients, add the middleware:

                                    connection = Faraday.new do |f|
  f.request :correlation_tracker
  f.adapter Faraday.default_adapter
end

For more information, visit:
  https://github.com/promobi/correlation_tracker

===============================================================================